In addition, Info has a copy constructor:
    inline Info(const Info& o)
      : name_(o.name_)
        , baseTime_(o.baseTime_.load())
        , nestingCount_(o.nestingCount_.load())
        , cycleCount_(o.cycleCount_.load())
        , duration_(o.duration_.load()) {
      CHECK_EQ(o.nestingCount_, 0U);
    }

I am not challenging the atomic class.
This appears to be due to the hash table implementation you're using trying to execute an explicit assignment: "__cache->__value_ = *__first;" when inserting the item, where the gcc and msvc implementations uses a copy constructor, which is implemented.

try changing the line:

timing_[shapes][mode] = tm;

to:

timing_[shapes].insert(std::make_pair(mode, tm));

@mjmg if you do not want to use full mkl (core), please try the following.

export MKLROOT=/usr/local (change to location where you have MKL2017/MKLML , not full MKL)

the above export will bypass downloading MKLML/MKL2017, and will just use your location.

please build with,
make -j $(nproc) USE_OPENCV=1 USE_MKL2017=1 USE_MKL2017_EXPERIMENTAL=1 USE_BLAS=

The above will build with BLAS set to MKLML and LAPACK enabled by default. The empty USE_BLAS will force the build to use MKLML's blas.
